{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban third party educators from teaching RHSE in schools and producing resources",
        "additional_details": "Many parents are growing increasingly worried about what their children are being taught in our nation's schools.\r\n \r\nWe are seeing examples and hearing reports from parents and teachers about age inappropriate materials being used for children as young as six, including around gender identity.\r\n \r\nWe believe that most of these problems are being caused by third party educators who are teaching and creating resources.",
        "background": "We believe that only qualified teachers should teach RHSE in schools and that only they or the UK Government should produce resources for teaching the subject. This will help ensure that content is age appropriate and in line with the curriculum.",
